	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>THE SHADOW FALLS:TWILIGHT CHAPTER 5</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'><html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage Express 2.0">
<title>Untitled </title>
</head>

<body>

<p><marquee>*(A Thesis of The Cruel Angel), Like an angel that has no sense of mercy..., Rise, young child, to the heavens like a legend... Cold winds, as blue as the sea.Tear open the door to your heart, I see... But unknowing you seem, just staring at me... Standing there smiling serenely. Desperate, for something to touch... A moment of kindness like that in a dream... Your innocent eyes, have yet no idea... Of the path your destiny will follow... But someday you'll become aware of... Everything that you've got behind you...Your wings are for seeking out a new... Future that only you can search for. The cruel angel's thesis bleeds through a portal like your pulsing blood. If you should betray the chapel of your memories, Cruel angel's thesis enters.....through the window of your soul So, child, stand tall and embrace the fire of the legend. Embracing the universe like a blazing star!</marquee>
</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">---------------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Chapter 5 Rumble at Highpass</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">---------------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Night begins falls on the nightmarish forest
of Kithicore, the tired trio ventures on up the Highpass
Mountains, hoping to make to shelter before it is too dark to
continue forward.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">The sounds of Tenrou&#146;s stomach
reverberate loudly.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I am so hungry! I wish I could have
gotten a chance to get my stuff before we left.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;And risk getting caught after all we
did to get out?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I could have made it. I did learn the
ways of a scout! I can sneak anywhere.&#148; His stomach grumbles
again. &#147;..if I wasn&#146;t so hungry.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;You should have planned for an
emergency. Isn&#146;t that right Reyas..Reyas? Where&#146;d you
go?&quot;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">/..I&#146;m sleeping..Lemme alone./</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;AAH No you don&#146;t! Come on get of
there! If we have to walk, we ALL are going to walk.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">/......zzzzzzzzz....../</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;GET UP!&#148; Leylia shakes her
pendant violently.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">/All right! All right!/ The pendant shines
brightly illuminating the darkening sky and Reyas appears in
front of them. He gives Leylia an evil glare.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;You just want all of us to suffer
don&#146;t you.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Yep.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;.....you&#146;re too much like your
mother....Speaking of suffering. Tenrou, how exactly are you
going to get inside the fort? We are not going to stay outside
all day and dark elves tend to attract a lot of negative
attention round these parts.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I thought you would never ask.&#148;
He reaches into a pocket in his cloak and pulls out a small ring.
He puts it on and his dark skin begins to flicker away. In a
moment, he features have blurred and paled into that of a human
male.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">He turns to them showing his new look.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Taaadaa!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;eeeewww. You look terrible.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Well. What can you expect? It&#146;s a
simple ring enchanted to make the bearer look human. Not that
humans are the best-looking creatures in existence. I prefer us
elves myself.&#148; He says while winking at Leylia, making her
blush slightly.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;HEY! HEY! None of that!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;None of what?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;You know what I&#146;m talking about
Tenrou!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;O. Seems like someone is a bit
jealous.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Why you little!&#148; Reyas leaps out
at Tenrou, who easily sidesteps out of the way and begins to dash
up the path towards Highpass Hold. Leylia just laughed and
laughed as they over her.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">---------------------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Deep into the night, the trio finally makes
it the gates of Highpass Hold. The protector of the eastern and
western lands from invaders and dissidents. The high towers are
well garrisoned by troops always on watch for raids by gnolls,
orcs and undead hordes.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;HALT!! WHO GOES THERE!!!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Just three really tired and hungry
travelers trying to get to Qeynos!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;A likely story. Do not move!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Ok!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;They wait silently as one of the
guards moves from the towers and onto the wall of the Hold. He
disappears for a moment as he bends down to pick up something,
then a bright light shines down across the pass, as the guard
holds a wisp lamp above his head.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Enter with you hands above your head
and any weapons you are carrying at your side!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Before they can reply, the light is gone and
the sounds of the heavy steel gates being opened, moves over
them. Following the guard's orders they enter into the hold and
are paraded around and inspected roughly before they are set
free.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Must they treat people so rough?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Can&#146;t blame them really. This is
quite a dangerous area, especially at night. Who knows what lurks
within the shadows. Ever since Bloody Kithicore, nothing has been
the same; the undead thrive amongst the woods we just left. Not
to mention the clans of orcs and gnolls that are plotting to
overtake the Hold so the can raid the unsuspecting cities and
villages below. This is not exactly a dream assignment for a
soldier. You&#146;re chances of survival are 1 in 2. Which is one
of two things that really concerns me Leylia.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;What&#146;s that?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;One. Because of the hazards here, most
of the guards here are convicts and people not wanted in the
other cities. Who knows what&#146;s on there thieving minds.
Which brings up concern two. Where&#146;s Tenrou?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Huh?&#148; She looks around. &#147;I
thought he was right behind us&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Me too. O well. Lets just go to a
tavern and try to get a room or something to eat. We&#146;ll let
him find us.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Sounds, good I am so hungry!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">-------------------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">The HighNoon Tavern was still open and
bustling with activity. Scrounging what platinum they had left,
they purchased some food and mead. Reyas and Leylia sat at the
bar enjoying it, patiently waiting on Tenrou to return. In the
meantime, the mead went straight to Leylia&#146;s head and she
was quite drunk.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;*hic*..One ..more Reya..*hic*. I like
this..stuf.....&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I think you&#146;ve had enough. I
guess I should get you up to a room.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;You..sho gwood tooo me..Re-Re.. your
cinaa qute whin your win dis fworm...qwis me!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Hehe..O.boy. You have definitely had a
bit too much. Time for bed.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Ahh. Yourr. No...
fonn...zzzzzzzzzz...&#148; She passed out and fell into his lap.
&#147;O boy, what would Raziel say, if he saw this?&#148;At that
moment a hand taps Reyas on the shoulder.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Am I interrupting something?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;!!!!! NO! We where just waiting on
you!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Ah-huh.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Where have you been Tenrou?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Taking care of some business. Speaking
of which, I got us a room not far from here.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;That&#146;s good. Leylia&#146;s out
cold.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Well, pick her up, and I&#146;ll show
you to the room.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">------------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Leylia&#146;s snoring could be heard loudly
outside on the balcony where Tenrou and Reyas, stand looking out
over the Hold.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Does she always snore this loud?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Only when she&#146;s drunk.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;And how many times have you gotten her
drunk?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;This would be the first time.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Ahhhh.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Aside for her snoring, she looks so
peaceful. It&#146;s heard to believe that she has such a fate in
front of her.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;You really care about her don&#146;t
you Reyas?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Of course, it&#146;s my duty and my
promise.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;You know what I mean.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;No. I can&#146;t, I am just her
protector, her guardian, at the most her friend. I can&#146;t
seek or want anything more. That is for someone else.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;If you say so.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I do say so. Any way, what where you
doing, where did you go earlier?&#148;<br
style="mso-special-character:line-break">
</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I told you to handle a little
business, and I came here to get this room.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Sure..&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;It&#146;s not I like I...Hey what does
the ringing of that bell mean?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">As Reyas notices the ringing of a bell, he
catches a flurry of activity at the wall facing toward Kithicore
Forrest, out of the corner of his eye.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;The Hold is under attack!&#148; They
both say, as Tenrou looks along the wall facing towards the
plains of Karana.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Tenrou, I&#146;ll help the garrison on
the Kithicore Wall, you help the Karana wall.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Ok let&#146;s go!&#148; They reenter
the room and lock the windows and door to keep Leylia inside and
head out to help in the defense of HighPass Hold.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Reyas arrives first at a tower overlooking
the pass from Kithicore forest. A moment later, the sound of
rotting flesh and bone plodding along the ground, and the smell
of death fills the air as the first of the undead waves emerge.
The garrisoned troops light arrows and oil satchels and wait for
the undead to draw closer.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">At that same moment Tenrou arrives at the
sealed wall overlooking the pass to Karana plains. The troops
there also begin light arrows and satchels. The begin moving pots
filled with boiling water and pitch up to the front of wall just
as the first few lines of Mucktail gnolls begin the assault.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;LOOSE!&#148; Is heard being shouted
across the Hold, followed by the searing light of flames the
piercing screams of those below, being torn asunder.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Again and again flaming arrows leap dash
across the night sky, carving the attackers into bits on and on
through the night.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">------------------------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">As day breaks, the last of Gnolls and the
undead retreat back into their respective homes. And the smoke
and dust begins to clear from the battle. Screams fill the air
again, but this time of celebration as for now the Hold is
intact.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Tenrou stretches out on the wall, taking a
deserved rest like the other hundreds of soldiers and volunteers.
Reyas eventually wanders by with Leylia, who had slept soundly
through the whole thing.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Hey Tenrou. You make out ok?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Yeah it was easy. Not one gnoll made
to the wall, but they just didn&#146;t know when to give up. They
kept coming, coming. Oy.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Well at no one in the Hold was
seriously hurt. Say it looks like we all could use some breakfast
before we get back on the trail.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Nice idea, but we are all out of
money&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;That&#146;s ok, the owner of the Ye
Old High time, is having a celebration for the victory, free food
for every one!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Tenrou looks worried. &#147;Did you say the
Ye Old High Time?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Yeah. Why?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Umm...nothing. Lets go get some
breakfast!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Alright!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">A few moments later, they are mingling with
the crowd, which is bursting with excitement over the victory.
The three finds a space at the bar and enjoys a hearty meal,
until the owner walks by Tenrou.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;YOU! YOU DIRTY THEIVING
SCOUNDREL!!!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;O boy..Run!!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">The owner and several other patrons try to
grab them but they manage to slip by.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Tenrou!! What in the hell did you
do!?!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Well.. I sort of..umm...deprived the
owner of a few funds and..umm..other stuff.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;TENROU! What kind of lousy thief are
you!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Well I&#146;m sorry! I just was trying
to get some money for a room. And how was I supposed to know that
that girl was the pub owner...&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;TENROU!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I didn&#146;t think she was going to
mind, she had so much, I didn&#146;t think she would miss
it.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I&#146;ll hurt you later! Lets just
get out before they lock us in!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;GUARDS STOP THEM!!! CLOSE THE
GATE!!!!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">A few arrows whiz past them as they make a
mad dash for the gate to the plains of Karana and just barely
squeeze through.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;STOP COME BACK HERE!!! I&#148;LL GET
YOU! YOU DIRTY LOUSY THEIVING...&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Her voice fades out as they continue to dash
out into the distance.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">---------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Tenrou.....Remind me ....to
maim..you..once we get to Qeynos..&#148; Leylia says while
catching her breath.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I&#146;m sorry guys. I thought we
would have left before any one found out. I was just trying to
get us a room and food.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Uh-huh.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I&#146;m serious, but we do have a
problem now. They&#146;ll send bounty hunters after us, and they
are looking for a darkly tanned wood elf girl, a human male, and
half elf male.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Yeah, so?&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Tenrou turns and looks at Reyas </p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;They wont be looking for a human guy
travelling with two girls.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;So, where are we going to find
another.....O No ! NO NO! NO!!! NOT A CHANCE!!!&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">----------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;Cheer up Reyas, you look good like
that. The blouse really matches your eyes&#148; Leylia says while
suppressing her laugher.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&#147;I hate you guys, I really do.&#148;</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">-----------------------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">End of This Chapter!</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">-----------------------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">------------------------------------------</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Preview of Next Chapter (Spoiler Alert!)</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">The trio finally arrives at the human
citadel fo Qeynos, and just when they think they can rest,
Veeshan rears her head again. The secrets and mysteries of the
Twilight and more will be revealed in the next exciting chapter:
Scorched Earth!</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
